/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ourPrivacy notice\", \"from\": 327, \"to\": 344}, {\"ngram\": \"controversy\", \"from\": 388, \"to\": 399}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic prize money\", \"from\": 405, \"to\": 424}, {\"ngram\": \"a dire warning\", \"from\": 438, \"to\": 452}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"existential threat\", \"from\": 458, \"to\": 481}, {\"ngram\": \"climate change\", \"from\": 486, \"to\": 500}, {\"ngram\": \"a wide-ranging press conference\", \"from\": 504, \"to\": 535}, {\"ngram\": \"the first day\", \"from\": 539, \"to\": 552}, {\"ngram\": \"athletics action inParis\", \"from\": 556, \"to\": 580}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In April, Lord Coe's organisation became the first sport governing body to announce it would be awarding prize money to Olympic champions, with $50,000United Statesdollars going to gold medallists in Paris, with the ambition of lesser amounts to be awarded to athletes who collect silver and bronze atLos Angeles2028.\", \"from\": 584, \"to\": 901, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 594, \"end\": 602, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lord Coe\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\"}, {\"begin\": 784, \"end\": 789, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999890861, \"rank\": 1.0949480711022094e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"April\", \"from\": 587, \"to\": 592}, {\"ngram\": \"the first sport governing body\", \"from\": 625, \"to\": 655}, {\"ngram\": \"prize money\", \"from\": 689, \"to\": 700}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic champions\", \"from\": 704, \"to\": 721}, {\"ngram\": \"$50,000United Statesdollars\", \"from\": 728, \"to\": 755}, {\"ngram\": \"gold medallists\", \"from\": 765, \"to\": 780}, {\"ngram\": \"the ambition\", \"from\": 796, \"to\": 808}, {\"ngram\": \"lesser amounts\", \"from\": 812, \"to\": 826}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 844, \"to\": 852}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 865, \"to\": 871}, {\"ngram\": \"bronze\", \"from\": 876, \"to\": 882}, {\"ngram\": \"atLos Angeles2028\", \"from\": 883, \"to\": 900}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 67-year-old Briton, who in August ran unopposed for a third term, did not flatly rule out whether or not he would consider eventually campaigning for theInternational Olympic Committeepresidency but reiterated his commitment to the current cause.\", \"from\": 903, \"to\": 1153, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The 67-year-old Briton\", \"from\": 903, \"to\": 925}, {\"ngram\": \"August\", \"from\": 934, \"to\": 940}, {\"ngram\": \"a third term\", \"from\": 959, \"to\": 971}, {\"ngram\": \"theInternational Olympic Committeepresidency\", \"from\": 1057, \"to\": 1101}, {\"ngram\": \"his commitment\", \"from\": 1117, \"to\": 1131}, {\"ngram\": \"the current cause\", \"from\": 1135, \"to\": 1152}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I find nothing particularly strange about it (athletics prize money in Paris) and we are not the only ones funding athletes Addressing the prize money, Lord Coe said: \\\"I am really surprised if people do not see the correlation between athletes of high profile that are comfortable and whose welfare is being looked after, and their ability to perform and raise the profile of the sport and add to the broadcast revenues and the sponsorships that come in.\", \"from\": 1155, \"to\": 1610, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1226, \"end\": 1231, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999890861, \"rank\": 1.0949480711022094e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1308, \"end\": 1316, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lord Coe\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"nothing\", \"from\": 1162, \"to\": 1169}, {\"ngram\": \"(athletics prize money\", \"from\": 1200, \"to\": 1222}, {\"ngram\": \"the only ones\", \"from\": 1248, \"to\": 1261}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1270, \"to\": 1278}, {\"ngram\": \"the prize money\", \"from\": 1290, \"to\": 1305}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 1348, \"to\": 1354}, {\"ngram\": \"the correlation\", \"from\": 1366, \"to\": 1381}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1390, \"to\": 1398}, {\"ngram\": \"high profile\", \"from\": 1402, \"to\": 1414}, {\"ngram\": \"whose welfare\", \"from\": 1440, \"to\": 1453}, {\"ngram\": \"the profile\", \"from\": 1516, \"to\": 1527}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 1531, \"to\": 1540}, {\"ngram\": \"the broadcast revenues\", \"from\": 1552, \"to\": 1574}, {\"ngram\": \"the sponsorships\", \"from\": 1579, \"to\": 1595}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's not complicated to recognise that the athletes need to be reflected in those proceeds of growth.\", \"from\": 1612, \"to\": 1714, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 1652, \"to\": 1664}, {\"ngram\": \"those proceeds\", \"from\": 1689, \"to\": 1703}, {\"ngram\": \"growth\", \"from\": 1707, \"to\": 1713}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I find nothing particularly strange about it and we are not the only ones funding athletes.\", \"from\": 1715, \"to\": 1806, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"nothing\", \"from\": 1722, \"to\": 1729}, {\"ngram\": \"the only ones\", \"from\": 1775, \"to\": 1788}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1797, \"to\": 1805}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Well over 60 percent of national Olympic committees have done that for as long as I can remember.\\\"\", \"from\": 1807, \"to\": 1905, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"over 60 percent\", \"from\": 1812, \"to\": 1827}, {\"ngram\": \"national Olympic committees\", \"from\": 1831, \"to\": 1858}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Criticism has come from federations with much smaller coffers, concerned that the surprise move might put pressure on other sports to do the same.\", \"from\": 1907, \"to\": 2053, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Criticism\", \"from\": 1907, \"to\": 1916}, {\"ngram\": \"federations\", \"from\": 1931, \"to\": 1942}, {\"ngram\": \"much smaller coffers\", \"from\": 1948, \"to\": 1968}, {\"ngram\": \"the surprise move\", \"from\": 1985, \"to\": 2002}, {\"ngram\": \"pressure\", \"from\": 2013, \"to\": 2021}, {\"ngram\": \"other sports\", \"from\": 2025, \"to\": 2037}]}, {\"sentence\": \"World Athletics CEO Jon Ridgeon added: \\\"They are the stars of the show, and if you look at our existing world championships beyond the Olympic Games, we were spending $24 million in prize money over four years of the cycle in our existing championships, and we just felt that our highest-profile event should be part of that.\\\"\", \"from\": 2055, \"to\": 2381, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2055, \"end\": 2070, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.717271047214686e-16, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 2075, \"end\": 2086, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jon_Ridgeon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jon Ridgeon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jon_Ridgeon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jon_Ridgeon\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the stars\", \"from\": 2104, \"to\": 2113}, {\"ngram\": \"the show\", \"from\": 2117, \"to\": 2125}, {\"ngram\": \"our existing world championships\", \"from\": 2146, \"to\": 2178}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 2186, \"to\": 2203}, {\"ngram\": \"prize money\", \"from\": 2237, \"to\": 2248}, {\"ngram\": \"four years\", \"from\": 2254, \"to\": 2264}, {\"ngram\": \"the cycle\", \"from\": 2268, \"to\": 2277}, {\"ngram\": \"our existing championships\", \"from\": 2281, \"to\": 2307}, {\"ngram\": \"our highest-profile event\", \"from\": 2331, \"to\": 2356}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 2367, \"to\": 2371}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ridgeon also confirmed that in a situation in which athletes decided to share a gold medal in Paris - such as that famously of Tokyo 2020 high jumpers and between pole vaulters Katie Moon and Nina Kennedy at last year's world championships - the prize money would be split.\", \"from\": 2383, \"to\": 2656, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2477, \"end\": 2482, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999890861, \"rank\": 1.0949480711022094e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2510, \"end\": 2515, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.990083525117349e-15, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2566, \"end\": 2570, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moon\", \"score\": 0.9999999958431545, \"rank\": 4.156737069950968e-09, \"text\": \"Moon\", \"types\": [\"Q634\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moon\"}, {\"begin\": 2575, \"end\": 2587, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nina_Gamble_Kennedy\", \"score\": 0.9999999631131693, \"rank\": 3.688689484561794e-08, \"text\": \"Nina Kennedy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nina_Gamble_Kennedy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nina_Gamble_Kennedy\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ridgeon\", \"from\": 2383, \"to\": 2390}, {\"ngram\": \"a situation\", \"from\": 2414, \"to\": 2425}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 2435, \"to\": 2443}, {\"ngram\": \"a gold medal\", \"from\": 2461, \"to\": 2473}, {\"ngram\": \"2020 high jumpers\", \"from\": 2516, \"to\": 2533}, {\"ngram\": \"pole vaulters\", \"from\": 2546, \"to\": 2559}, {\"ngram\": \"last year's world championships\", \"from\": 2591, \"to\": 2622}, {\"ngram\": \"the prize money\", \"from\": 2625, \"to\": 2640}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In Paris, 144 medals are up for grabs over 11 days of athletics action, beginning with Ecuadorian Brian Pintado's victory in the men's race walk on Thursday morning, when both the men's and women's individual competitions were delayed by weather.\", \"from\": 2658, \"to\": 2904, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2661, \"end\": 2666, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999890861, \"rank\": 1.0949480711022094e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2745, \"end\": 2755, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ecuadorians\", \"score\": 0.9864407772793213, \"rank\": 0.013743627887262142, \"text\": \"Ecuadorian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ecuadorians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ecuadorians\"}, {\"begin\": 2756, \"end\": 2769, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_Pintado\", \"score\": 0.9999756886936054, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Brian Pintado\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_Pintado\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_Pintado\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"144 medals\", \"from\": 2668, \"to\": 2678}, {\"ngram\": \"grabs\", \"from\": 2690, \"to\": 2695}, {\"ngram\": \"11 days\", \"from\": 2701, \"to\": 2708}, {\"ngram\": \"athletics action\", \"from\": 2712, \"to\": 2728}, {\"ngram\": \"Thursday morning\", \"from\": 2806, \"to\": 2822}, {\"ngram\": \"both the men's and women's individual competitions\", \"from\": 2829, \"to\": 2879}, {\"ngram\": \"weather\", \"from\": 2896, \"to\": 2903}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lord Coe has kept a keen eye on the forecast in Paris, where the equivalent of a typical July rainfall bore down in 36 hours, blighting the opening ceremony and contributing to the postponement of several events.\", \"from\": 2906, \"to\": 3118, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2906, \"end\": 2914, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lord Coe\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\"}, {\"begin\": 2954, \"end\": 2959, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999890861, \"rank\": 1.0949480711022094e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a keen eye\", \"from\": 2924, \"to\": 2934}, {\"ngram\": \"the forecast\", \"from\": 2938, \"to\": 2950}, {\"ngram\": \"36 hours\", \"from\": 3022, \"to\": 3030}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 3042, \"to\": 3062}, {\"ngram\": \"the postponement\", \"from\": 3083, \"to\": 3099}, {\"ngram\": \"several events\", \"from\": 3103, \"to\": 3117}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Men's triathlon was perhaps the most high-profile victim, with organisers postponing its start by a day after unsafe levels of E. Coli in the Seine.\", \"from\": 3120, \"to\": 3268, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3262, \"end\": 3267, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999807471979518, \"rank\": 1.9253159356986032e-05, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Men's triathlon\", \"from\": 3120, \"to\": 3135}, {\"ngram\": \"the most high-profile victim\", \"from\": 3148, \"to\": 3176}, {\"ngram\": \"organisers\", \"from\": 3183, \"to\": 3193}, {\"ngram\": \"its start\", \"from\": 3205, \"to\": 3214}, {\"ngram\": \"a day\", \"from\": 3218, \"to\": 3223}, {\"ngram\": \"unsafe levels\", \"from\": 3230, \"to\": 3243}, {\"ngram\": \"E. Coli\", \"from\": 3247, \"to\": 3254}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Last month, in a report published by the British Association for Sustainable Sport, Lord Coe wrote that \\\"climate change should increasingly be viewed as an existential threat to sport\\\".\", \"from\": 3270, \"to\": 3455, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3354, \"end\": 3362, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lord Coe\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a report\", \"from\": 3285, \"to\": 3293}, {\"ngram\": \"the British Association\", \"from\": 3307, \"to\": 3330}, {\"ngram\": \"Sustainable Sport\", \"from\": 3335, \"to\": 3352}, {\"ngram\": \"climate change\", \"from\": 3375, \"to\": 3389}, {\"ngram\": \"an existential threat\", \"from\": 3423, \"to\": 3444}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 3448, \"to\": 3453}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He expanded further in Paris, saying, \\\"I think sport is going to have to take some of these issues in our own hands, I do.\", \"from\": 3457, \"to\": 3579, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3480, \"end\": 3485, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999890861, \"rank\": 1.0949480711022094e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 3504, \"to\": 3509}, {\"ngram\": \"these issues\", \"from\": 3543, \"to\": 3555}, {\"ngram\": \"our own hands\", \"from\": 3559, \"to\": 3572}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I can not see us not having a root and branch review of the global calendar to deal with some of these issues.\", \"from\": 3580, \"to\": 3690, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 3594, \"to\": 3596}, {\"ngram\": \"a root and branch review\", \"from\": 3608, \"to\": 3632}, {\"ngram\": \"the global calendar\", \"from\": 3636, \"to\": 3655}, {\"ngram\": \"these issues\", \"from\": 3677, \"to\": 3689}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"When it comes to athletics, it's quite serious because we are talking about the welfare of the athletes, and maybe we are going to have to move some of our endurance events to other times of the year.\", \"from\": 3692, \"to\": 3893, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"athletics\", \"from\": 3710, \"to\": 3719}, {\"ngram\": \"the welfare\", \"from\": 3769, \"to\": 3780}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 3784, \"to\": 3796}, {\"ngram\": \"our endurance events\", \"from\": 3845, \"to\": 3865}, {\"ngram\": \"other times\", \"from\": 3869, \"to\": 3880}, {\"ngram\": \"the year\", \"from\": 3884, \"to\": 3892}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We do not always want to have to turn up as an international federation with a field hospital.\", \"from\": 3895, \"to\": 3990, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an international federation\", \"from\": 3940, \"to\": 3967}, {\"ngram\": \"a field hospital\", \"from\": 3973, \"to\": 3989}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We just need to make sure that if we are tru